<collectingCountry box="[854,986,272,298]" name="Philippines" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Philippines</collectingCountry>
Isl.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,152,418]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,275,311,337]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Notes.</emphasis>
Basal portion of elytra orange, elytral spots yellow. Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1938" box="[1016,1304,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1016,1256,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Scirtes basifasciatus</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
, but elytral suture black (orange in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1938" box="[431,614,352,378]" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[431,446,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[461,614,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">basifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), penis much longer than parameres (as long as parameres in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Scirtidae" genus="Scirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="basifasciatus">
<emphasis box="[1347,1361,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">basifasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), parameres short, with three pairs of small projections in lateral margins.
</paragraph>
